context: The word 'teinud' is the past participle of the verb 'teha', which means 'to do' or 'to make'. It is used with auxiliary verbs to form compound tenses, such as perfect and pluperfect. Commonly appears in sentences like 'I have done my homework' (Ma olen teinud oma kodutöö) or 'He has made a mistake' (Ta on teinud vea).
